This module is an independent implementation of the AutoRT system described in:

  M. Ahn, D. Dwibedi, C. Finn, M. G. Arenas, K. Gopalakrishnan, K. Hausman,
  B. Ichter, A. Irpan, N. Joshi, R. Julian, S. Kirmani, I. Leal, E. Lee,
  S. Levine, Y. Lu, I. Leal, S. Maddineni, K. Pertsch, Q. Vuong, A. Wahid,
  S. Welker, P. Wohlhart, F. Xia, T. Xiao, P. Xu, S. Xu, Z. Xu, Y. Zhou,
  and B. Zitkovich,
  "AutoRT: Embodied Foundation Models for Large Scale Orchestration of
  Robotic Agents", arXiv:2401.12963, 2024.
  https://arxiv.org/abs/2401.12963

No source code from the original AutoRT system was used. This is an
independent reimplementation based on the methods described in the paper,
adapted for dual AR4 robotic arms in a Unity simulation environment.

Key design decisions derived from the paper:
  - Continuous scene understanding → task generation → safety filtering → execution loop (AutoRTLoop.py)
  - LLM-based task generation from scene descriptions (TaskGenerator.py)
  - Robot Constitution two-layer safety: semantic LLM + kinematic code checks (RobotConstitution.py)
  - Balanced task selection across explore/exploit/random strategies (TaskSelector.py)
  - Human-in-the-loop approval (enabled by default)
